# Arweave Plugin Configuration
# Set your Arweave wallet private key here (optional but required for wallet operations)
# ARWEAVE_WALLET_KEY={"kty":"RSA","n":"...","e":"...","d":"...","p":"...","q":"...","dp":"...","dq":"...","qi":"..."}

### ARWEAVE NETWORK CONFIGURATION ###
# Choose between ArLocal (development) or Arweave mainnet (production)

# ArLocal Development Configuration (for local testing)
# Uncomment these lines to use ArLocal for development
ARWEAVE_GATEWAY=localhost
ARWEAVE_PORT=1984
ARWEAVE_PROTOCOL=http

# Arweave Mainnet Configuration (default - production)
# These are the default values if no configuration is provided
# ARWEAVE_GATEWAY=cu.ardrive.io
# ARWEAVE_PORT=443
# ARWEAVE_PROTOCOL=https

# Alternative Arweave Gateways (uncomment to use)
# ARWEAVE_GATEWAY=arweave.net
# ARWEAVE_PORT=443
# ARWEAVE_PROTOCOL=https

### ARLOCAL DEVELOPMENT NOTES ###
# When using ArLocal:
# 1. Start ArLocal: npx arlocal
# 2. ArLocal runs on http://localhost:1984
# 3. Use the mine endpoint to confirm transactions: curl http://localhost:1984/mine
# 4. Use the mint endpoint to add test tokens: curl http://localhost:1984/mint/{address}/{amount}
# 5. Transactions remain pending until manually mined
# 6. All data is stored locally and reset when ArLocal restarts

### CONFIGURATION SWITCHING ###
# To switch between ArLocal and mainnet:
# 1. For ArLocal: Set ARWEAVE_GATEWAY=localhost, ARWEAVE_PORT=1984, ARWEAVE_PROTOCOL=http
# 2. For mainnet: Remove ArLocal settings or set ARWEAVE_GATEWAY=cu.ardrive.io, ARWEAVE_PORT=443, ARWEAVE_PROTOCOL=https
# 3. Restart your application after changing configuration
